WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:11.883 --> 00:02:15.304
Ser Ryam was a strong
Lord Commander of the Kingsguard.

3
00:02:17.014 --> 00:02:18.974
But he was ill for some time.

4
00:02:19.057 --> 00:02:20.684
He passed in peace. I hope.

5
00:02:20.767 --> 00:02:21.767
Yes. Your Grace.

6
00:02:21.810 --> 00:02:24.813
He was found to have passed
gently in his sleep.

7
00:02:25.188 --> 00:02:28.400
His remains are being prepared
by the Silent Sisters.

8
00:02:28.483 --> 00:02:31.820
The succeeding Lord Commander.
Ser Harrold.

9
00:02:31.903 --> 00:02:33.613
would like to make haste in finding

10
00:02:33.697 --> 00:02:36.283
Ser Ryam's replacement
on the Kingsguard.

11
00:02:36.366 --> 00:02:38.368
Your Grace. My lords.

12
00:02:38.952 --> 00:02:41.955
The Kingsguard must soon be restored
to its full complement of seven.

13
00:02:43.248 --> 00:02:44.666
With the help of the Hand.

14
00:02:44.750 --> 00:02:47.252
I've invited a number
of fine candidates to court.

15
00:02:47.336 --> 00:02:49.296
All have passed fair trials.

16
00:02:53.592 --> 00:02:55.385
Four ships have now been lost.

17
00:02:55.469 --> 00:02:56.928
The last one was flying my banner.

18
00:02:57.846 --> 00:02:59.848
The Stepstones have now
grown into a conflagration.

19
00:02:59.931 --> 00:03:02.351
yet you sit here
and dither about court business.

20
00:03:02.434 --> 00:03:04.394
If you've something
to discuss. Lord Corlys...

21
00:03:04.478 --> 00:03:06.480
I want to know what is to be done

22
00:03:06.563 --> 00:03:08.482
about my ships and my men.

23
00:03:08.565 --> 00:03:09.941
The Crown will compensate you

24
00:03:10.025 --> 00:03:11.860
for your ship and crew.
and make an offering

25
00:03:11.943 --> 00:03:15.781
- to the men's families.
- I don't want compensation.

26
00:03:17.449 --> 00:03:19.826
I want to seize the Stepstones by force

27
00:03:19.910 --> 00:03:21.536
and burn out this Crabfeeder.

28
00:03:21.620 --> 00:03:24.373
I am not prepared to start
a war with the Free Cities.

29
00:03:24.456 --> 00:03:27.167
These pirates are not the Free Cities.

30
00:03:27.250 --> 00:03:30.420
Who do you think provides them
with their ships and tender?

31
00:03:30.796 --> 00:03:32.636
In all of its history.
my lord.

32
00:03:32.714 --> 00:03:34.591
the Seven Kingdoms have never entered

33
00:03:34.674 --> 00:03:36.385
open war with the Free Cities.

34
00:03:36.468 --> 00:03:38.095
Were that to happen.

35
00:03:38.178 --> 00:03:41.181
the losses would be incalculable.

36
00:03:44.976 --> 00:03:47.562
What reason does
the Crabfeeder have to fear us?

37
00:03:50.607 --> 00:03:53.151
The King's own brother has been allowed
to seize Dragonstone

38
00:03:53.235 --> 00:03:56.154
and fortify it with an army
of his Gold Cloaks.

39
00:03:56.238 --> 00:03:58.990
Daemon has squatted there
for over half a year

40
00:03:59.074 --> 00:04:00.951
without even a protest from the Crown.

41
00:04:01.034 --> 00:04:03.745
I'll caution you. Lord Corlys.

42
00:04:03.829 --> 00:04:07.374
a seat at the King's table
does not make you his equal.

43
00:04:10.836 --> 00:04:12.337
I have acted. Corlys.

44
00:04:13.588 --> 00:04:16.591
I've sent envoys to Pentos and Volantis

45
00:04:16.675 --> 00:04:18.635
to see if we might find common cause.

46
00:04:19.344 --> 00:04:21.763
Ships and men are at the ready.

47
00:04:22.556 --> 00:04:25.976
The Stepstones will be settled in time.

48
00:04:26.601 --> 00:04:28.854
You have dragonriders. Father.

49
00:04:35.318 --> 00:04:36.486
Send us.

50
00:04:41.324 --> 00:04:44.578
It isn't that simple. Rhaenyra.

51
00:04:44.661 --> 00:04:46.329
It would be a show of force.

52
00:04:46.830 --> 00:04:48.915
At least the Princess has a plan.

53
00:04:52.627 --> 00:04:55.172
- I only meant that we should at least...
- Perhaps. uh.

54
00:04:55.255 --> 00:04:59.509
there's some better use
for the Princess' talents. Your Grace.

55
00:05:02.179 --> 00:05:04.389
Why don't you take the Princess
to see about the new

56
00:05:04.473 --> 00:05:06.183
Kingsguard posting. Lord Commander?

57
00:05:07.976 --> 00:05:09.561
A fine idea. Your Grace.

58
00:05:11.521 --> 00:05:14.107
This knight will protect you as well.

59
00:05:14.191 --> 00:05:15.442
You should choose.

60
00:05:36.379 --> 00:05:38.423
Ser Desmond Caron.

61
00:05:38.507 --> 00:05:40.926
a fine knight. Princess.

62
00:05:41.009 --> 00:05:43.011
Step forward. Ser Desmond.

63
00:05:45.222 --> 00:05:46.806
Son of Ser Royce Caron.

64
00:05:46.890 --> 00:05:49.434
Ser Desmond has proved strong and steady

65
00:05:49.518 --> 00:05:52.437
in both the tourney lists and without.

66
00:05:52.521 --> 00:05:55.357
While traveling through the Kingswood
on his way to King's Landing.

67
00:05:55.440 --> 00:05:58.401
Ser Desmond recently brought
a would-be poacher

68
00:05:58.485 --> 00:05:59.694
to justice.

69
00:06:10.413 --> 00:06:13.959
You might thank him
for his leal service. Princess.

70
00:06:14.042 --> 00:06:17.045
We thank you for your
loyal service to the Crown. ser.

71
00:06:28.765 --> 00:06:30.767
Ser Rymun Mallister.

72
00:06:33.103 --> 00:06:36.022
Son of Lord Lymond Mallister of Seagard.

73
00:06:36.106 --> 00:06:38.191
Winner of the melee at Cider Hall.

74
00:06:38.650 --> 00:06:41.444
He was the last mounted
of three-and-twenty knights.

75
00:06:41.528 --> 00:06:43.572
Ser Rymun was knighted at eight-and-ten.

76
00:06:43.655 --> 00:06:45.824
Do any of these knights
have combat experience?

77
00:06:47.200 --> 00:06:49.035
Beyond capturing poachers.

78
00:06:57.127 --> 00:06:59.129
Ser Criston Cole.

79
00:07:05.093 --> 00:07:08.096
Son of the steward
of the Lord of Blackhaven.

80
00:07:10.223 --> 00:07:12.017
Be welcome. Ser Criston.

81
00:07:14.311 --> 00:07:16.563
You saw combat in the Stormlands.

82
00:07:16.646 --> 00:07:18.815
Dornish marches. Princess.

83
00:07:18.898 --> 00:07:22.068
I fought for a year as a foot solider
against the Dornish incursions.

84
00:07:23.153 --> 00:07:25.113
Ser Arlan Dondarrion
knighted me after we razed

85
00:07:25.196 --> 00:07:27.198
two of the watchtowers
along the Boneway.

86
00:07:32.829 --> 00:07:34.581
I choose Ser Criston Cole.

87
00:07:35.040 --> 00:07:38.168
Let's not be too hasty. Princess.

88
00:07:39.294 --> 00:07:42.380
There's no doubt Ser Criston
is a fine warrior.

89
00:07:42.464 --> 00:07:44.924
but houses
such as Crakehall and Mallister

90
00:07:45.008 --> 00:07:47.594
are important allies of the Crown.

91
00:07:47.677 --> 00:07:50.388
Seagard. for instance.
is the realm's prime defense

92
00:07:50.472 --> 00:07:52.140
against reavers from the Iron Islands.

93
00:07:52.223 --> 00:07:53.850
Those men
are tourney knights.

94
00:07:54.392 --> 00:07:57.395
My father should be defended by a man
who's known real combat.

95
00:07:59.481 --> 00:08:00.690
Should he not?

96
00:08:02.901 --> 00:08:04.736
Of course. Princess.

97
00:08:04.819 --> 00:08:07.447
Well. let us plan Ser Criston's
investiture then.

98
00:08:15.872 --> 00:08:18.792
The Valyrian capital
was built into a volcano.

99
00:08:18.875 --> 00:08:20.418
much like Dragonstone.

100
00:08:21.419 --> 00:08:24.464
And the dragonlords.
the highest of the nobility.

101
00:08:24.547 --> 00:08:27.467
lived here. at the volcanic face.

102
00:08:27.550 --> 00:08:30.720
closest to the source
of their magic and power.

103
00:08:30.804 --> 00:08:32.639
And this was the Anogrion.

104
00:08:34.766 --> 00:08:36.976
Where the bloodmages worked their craft.

105
00:08:39.562 --> 00:08:41.773
It is truly wondrous what you've built.

106
00:08:41.856 --> 00:08:42.941
Oh. no.

107
00:08:44.192 --> 00:08:47.737
I only pore over the histories
and provide the plans.

108
00:08:47.821 --> 00:08:50.198
The stonemasons built the structures.

109
00:08:50.615 --> 00:08:53.493
Do you believe that Westeros
can be another Valyria. Your Grace?

110
00:08:53.576 --> 00:08:55.745
That depends.
whether you speak of the Freehold

111
00:08:55.829 --> 00:08:57.831
at its height or at its fall.

112
00:08:59.249 --> 00:09:00.917
Over a thousand dragons.

113
00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:04.003
a navy large enough to span
the seas of the world.

114
00:09:07.173 --> 00:09:10.176
The glory of Old Valyria
will never be seen again.

115
00:09:11.344 --> 00:09:12.971
Seven hells.

116
00:09:28.778 --> 00:09:30.572
Tell me. how is Rhaenyra?

117
00:09:31.239 --> 00:09:32.907
- What do you mean?
- Well. these days.

118
00:09:32.991 --> 00:09:35.368
she doesn't say more
than a few words to me.

119
00:09:35.744 --> 00:09:37.996
I think she might find it difficult

120
00:09:39.289 --> 00:09:41.291
to discuss personal matters.

121
00:09:42.959 --> 00:09:44.210
It will take time.

122
00:09:46.379 --> 00:09:48.256
It did when I lost mine own mother.

123
00:09:54.596 --> 00:09:56.598
I wish
she would approach me.

124
00:09:58.183 --> 00:09:59.476
What if you went to her?

125
00:10:00.435 --> 00:10:02.228
There are times when I would rather face

126
00:10:02.312 --> 00:10:05.106
the Black Dread himself
than mine own daughter of 15.

127
00:10:08.526 --> 00:10:11.529
I think she would open herself
to you if invited.

128
00:10:12.489 --> 00:10:15.909
You do have such an easy way about you.
Your Grace.

129
00:10:19.996 --> 00:10:22.999
You do not mention our talks
to Rhaenyra. do you?

130
00:10:25.418 --> 00:10:26.628
I just.

131
00:10:27.962 --> 00:10:30.089
I fear that she wouldn't
understand them.

132
00:10:30.840 --> 00:10:32.467
No. Your Grace.

133
00:10:45.980 --> 00:10:48.691
It's only been half a year
since my mother died.

134
00:10:48.775 --> 00:10:50.777
and already they tried
to marry my father off

135
00:10:50.860 --> 00:10:53.029
and replace me as heir.

136
00:10:53.112 --> 00:10:55.156
I know those men and how they plot

137
00:10:55.240 --> 00:10:58.451
in their secret councils
when I've been sent away.

138
00:10:58.535 --> 00:11:01.496
You cannot worry at the matters
of lords and kings. Rhaenyra.

139
00:11:04.290 --> 00:11:06.167
What if your father were to remarry?

140
00:11:14.801 --> 00:11:16.094
Your father loves you.

141
00:11:22.892 --> 00:11:24.894
He chose you for his heir.

142
00:11:26.020 --> 00:11:28.648
He didn't choose me. He spurns Daemon.

143
00:11:46.207 --> 00:11:47.834
Kneel with me.

144
00:12:04.893 --> 00:12:06.853
I find this is a way
to be with my mother.

145
00:12:09.230 --> 00:12:11.232
Here in the quiet of the Sept.

146
00:12:12.609 --> 00:12:13.776
I feel close to her.

147
00:12:19.532 --> 00:12:23.161
- I know it sounds foolish.
- I don't think it's foolish.

148
00:12:24.329 --> 00:12:26.331
- I don't.
- Good.

149
00:12:29.751 --> 00:12:31.753
Because I thought you might try.

150
00:12:35.089 --> 00:12:38.635
If not for me. then. perhaps for them.

151
00:13:04.118 --> 00:13:06.120
What do I say?

152
00:13:06.871 --> 00:13:08.498
Whatever you wish.

153
00:13:09.707 --> 00:13:11.542
It's only for you and the gods to know.

154
00:13:46.744 --> 00:13:50.039
I want him to see me
as more than his little girl.

155
00:13:52.583 --> 00:13:55.003
Mine own father does not know
the language of girls either.

156
00:14:00.049 --> 00:14:02.010
When I wish to talk with him.

157
00:14:02.927 --> 00:14:05.138
I know that I must make the effort.

158
00:14:08.850 --> 00:14:09.851
Thank you.

159
00:14:22.196 --> 00:14:24.073
Your Grace.

160
00:14:24.157 --> 00:14:25.575
I'm glad we could meet.

161
00:14:26.284 --> 00:14:27.869
I know tempers ran hot today.

162
00:14:27.952 --> 00:14:30.038
and I wanted to assure you
how much I value the bond

163
00:14:30.121 --> 00:14:31.748
between our houses.

164
00:14:32.206 --> 00:14:34.625
Rhaenys is my favorite cousin after all.

165
00:14:36.294 --> 00:14:39.255
I wish to apologize for the tenor

166
00:14:39.338 --> 00:14:41.632
at the Small Council today. Your Grace.

167
00:14:41.716 --> 00:14:43.384
It was not my intent to make offense.

168
00:14:44.594 --> 00:14:48.306
Your fleet is one of the realm's
most important assets. Lord Corlys.

169
00:14:48.848 --> 00:14:50.391
But you must understand.

170
00:14:50.475 --> 00:14:52.894
as King. it is my obligation
to avoid war

171
00:14:52.977 --> 00:14:55.188
until such time it is unavoidable.

172
00:14:55.271 --> 00:14:57.482
None among us desire open war.

173
00:14:59.108 --> 00:15:01.486
Might I speak plainly. Your Grace?

174
00:15:02.779 --> 00:15:06.157
I always welcome the unfettered thoughts
of my council.

175
00:15:06.240 --> 00:15:10.661
I fear that the eyes of our enemies
are presently fixed on the Red Keep.

176
00:15:11.454 --> 00:15:12.955
The Queen has passed.

177
00:15:13.039 --> 00:15:15.124
A girl has been named
heir to the Iron Throne.

178
00:15:15.208 --> 00:15:17.085
the first in its history.

179
00:15:17.168 --> 00:15:18.795
The King's brother. so disinherited.

180
00:15:18.878 --> 00:15:20.922
has claimed the Targaryen seat
on Dragonstone

181
00:15:21.005 --> 00:15:22.632
without challenge.

182
00:15:23.591 --> 00:15:26.177
And now. a foreign power
has established a colony

183
00:15:26.260 --> 00:15:28.471
in our most critical shipping lane.

184
00:15:29.722 --> 00:15:33.226
You paint such an aspirant portrait
of my reign. Lord Corlys.

185
00:15:33.309 --> 00:15:35.311
It is an honest one. cousin.

186
00:15:36.521 --> 00:15:39.565
At the moment. the Crown is perceived
as being vulnerable.

187
00:15:40.399 --> 00:15:42.318
And a blind incursion in the Stepstones

188
00:15:42.401 --> 00:15:44.654
is the only way to demonstrate
that we are not?

189
00:15:44.737 --> 00:15:48.282
To elude a storm.
you can either sail into it.

190
00:15:48.366 --> 00:15:49.951
or around it.

191
00:15:50.034 --> 00:15:52.578
But you must never await its coming.

192
00:15:53.955 --> 00:15:56.707
Do you have a specific
course of action to propose.

193
00:15:56.791 --> 00:15:58.417
my lord?

194
00:16:00.962 --> 00:16:02.839
Join our families.

195
00:16:03.548 --> 00:16:05.174
Wed our daughter. Laena.

196
00:16:05.258 --> 00:16:08.469
Unite the two great surviving
Valyrian houses.

197
00:16:08.553 --> 00:16:11.764
With the Targaryen dragons
and the Velaryon fleet bound in blood.

198
00:16:11.848 --> 00:16:13.307
you can show the realm

199
00:16:13.391 --> 00:16:16.144
that the Crown's strongest days
are ahead.

200
00:16:16.227 --> 00:16:17.395
not behind.

201
00:16:22.275 --> 00:16:23.901
I must admit.

202
00:16:24.527 --> 00:16:26.529
I haven't given marriage much thought.

203
00:16:27.238 --> 00:16:29.532
It hasn't even been half a year
since Aemma passed.

204
00:16:29.615 --> 00:16:33.161
The realm expects you to take a new wife
soon or late. Your Grace.

205
00:16:33.244 --> 00:16:36.372
to strengthen your line
and produce more heirs.

206
00:16:36.455 --> 00:16:39.667
You could not ask
for a stronger match than Laena.

207
00:17:07.653 --> 00:17:09.864
We haven't spoken much...

208
00:17:12.533 --> 00:17:13.784
since.

209
00:17:17.246 --> 00:17:18.915
A regret of mine.

210
00:17:20.583 --> 00:17:24.170
We should be free to speak our minds
to one another.

211
00:17:24.253 --> 00:17:25.796
You can say whatever you'd like.

212
00:17:25.880 --> 00:17:27.632
You are the King.

213
00:17:35.806 --> 00:17:39.852
I loved your mother very much.

214
00:17:43.147 --> 00:17:44.565
As did I.

215
00:18:00.873 --> 00:18:03.918
Ser Harrold provided
a fine field of tourney knights.

216
00:18:04.001 --> 00:18:05.001
Oh?

217
00:18:06.462 --> 00:18:08.089
But in questioning them.

218
00:18:08.172 --> 00:18:10.800
I discovered that Ser Criston
was the only man among them

219
00:18:10.883 --> 00:18:12.885
with true battle experience.

220
00:18:13.844 --> 00:18:16.472
He'll make a fine
knight of the Kingsguard.

221
00:18:21.894 --> 00:18:25.481
- Today at Small Council...
- Pay it no mind.

222
00:18:25.564 --> 00:18:27.149
I thought I might have had
some insight.

223
00:18:27.233 --> 00:18:28.401
You're young.

224
00:18:29.485 --> 00:18:30.695
You will learn.

225
00:18:55.428 --> 00:18:59.056
This is our best chance
to save the digit. Your Grace.

226
00:19:01.100 --> 00:19:03.227
The maggots will remove the dead flesh

227
00:19:03.311 --> 00:19:05.896
and hopefully stop the advance
of the rot.

228
00:19:11.694 --> 00:19:14.405
I held an audience earlier today

229
00:19:14.488 --> 00:19:16.657
with Lord Corlys and Princess Rhaenys.

230
00:19:16.741 --> 00:19:18.909
That was most charitable
of you. Your Grace.

231
00:19:18.993 --> 00:19:21.912
I'm sure Lord Corlys
appreciated the spirit of it.

232
00:19:22.371 --> 00:19:24.373
He proposed a marriage.

233
00:19:25.708 --> 00:19:28.002
To whom. Your Grace?

234
00:19:28.711 --> 00:19:30.296
The Lady Laena.

235
00:19:31.088 --> 00:19:33.174
To combine the strength of our houses.

236
00:19:33.674 --> 00:19:36.552
and demonstrate my reign's
strongest days are ahead.

237
00:19:36.635 --> 00:19:37.928
not behind.

238
00:19:38.012 --> 00:19:40.890
Lord Corlys has overreached. Your Grace.

239
00:19:40.973 --> 00:19:44.435
Such matters must be discussed
with the Small Council.

240
00:19:44.518 --> 00:19:47.271
That is what I'm doing. presently.

241
00:19:48.773 --> 00:19:52.401
So. what is your advice. dear Otto.

242
00:19:53.444 --> 00:19:55.071
The Lady Laena

243
00:19:55.946 --> 00:19:58.866
is young. Your Grace.

244
00:19:58.949 --> 00:20:01.952
Indeed. but the wounds
made by the Great Council

245
00:20:02.036 --> 00:20:03.829
still linger. my king.

246
00:20:03.913 --> 00:20:07.166
A match with their daughter
would go a long way towards

247
00:20:07.249 --> 00:20:08.793
sealing the breach

248
00:20:09.335 --> 00:20:12.213
and uniting the two great
Valyrian houses

249
00:20:12.296 --> 00:20:15.758
would certainly signal unity
throughout the realm

250
00:20:15.841 --> 00:20:17.426
and beyond.

251
00:20:18.094 --> 00:20:20.513
The Grand Maester's reasoning is sound.

252
00:20:22.348 --> 00:20:24.141
I do fear what Rhaenyra might think.

253
00:20:24.225 --> 00:20:26.143
What does it matter.
Your Grace?

254
00:20:26.227 --> 00:20:27.561
Her mother has passed.

255
00:20:28.646 --> 00:20:31.065
Her father must propagate
the royal line.

256
00:20:38.114 --> 00:20:42.118
I. uh. dearly loved my own lady wife.

257
00:20:43.160 --> 00:20:46.163
The pain of her passing still haunts me.

258
00:20:47.873 --> 00:20:49.875
And to be compelled to...

259
00:20:51.043 --> 00:20:53.671
replace her for duty's sake.

260
00:20:55.339 --> 00:20:56.966
You are the King.

261
00:20:58.008 --> 00:21:00.010
But I do not envy you.

262
00:21:28.831 --> 00:21:31.375
What was it like flying the Black Dread?

263
00:21:31.459 --> 00:21:34.420
You were Balerion's last rider.

264
00:21:34.920 --> 00:21:38.299
Only for a short time before he died.

265
00:21:38.382 --> 00:21:41.969
With Balerion died the last memory
of Valyria of Old.

266
00:21:42.887 --> 00:21:44.722
But Vhagar still lives

267
00:21:45.431 --> 00:21:46.849
somewhere.

268
00:21:46.932 --> 00:21:48.934
Bit too large for the Dragonpit.

269
00:21:49.477 --> 00:21:52.104
Some would say too large for our world.

270
00:21:52.980 --> 00:21:56.066
- Do you know where she nests?
- I'm sorry?

271
00:21:56.150 --> 00:21:58.152
Do you know where Vhagar is now?

272
00:21:58.235 --> 00:22:00.946
Uh. the Dragonkeepers believe
she made home

273
00:22:01.030 --> 00:22:03.449
somewhere on the coast
of the Narrow Sea.

274
00:22:03.532 --> 00:22:07.161
The workers at Spicetown report
hearing her song at times.

275
00:22:07.244 --> 00:22:09.455
They say it is a sad thing.

276
00:22:11.248 --> 00:22:13.250
I imagine even dragons get lonely.

277
00:22:17.838 --> 00:22:19.173
Your Grace.

278
00:22:20.341 --> 00:22:22.301
it would be a great honor

279
00:22:22.384 --> 00:22:26.555
to join our houses
as they were in Old Valyria.

280
00:22:26.639 --> 00:22:29.850
I would give you many children
of pure Valyrian blood

281
00:22:29.934 --> 00:22:33.687
so that we might strengthen
the royal line and the realm.

282
00:22:33.771 --> 00:22:36.065
Is that what your father
told you to say?

283
00:22:41.028 --> 00:22:42.613
What did your mother tell you?

284
00:22:44.448 --> 00:22:47.660
That I wouldn't have to bed you
until I turned 14.

285
00:23:15.062 --> 00:23:16.564
It bothers you. does it not?

286
00:23:22.403 --> 00:23:24.029
My father is a king.

287
00:23:24.655 --> 00:23:27.908
It is his duty to take a new wife
and strengthen his line.

288
00:23:27.992 --> 00:23:30.720
I did not ask for a lesson in politics.
I asked whether this bothers you.

289
00:23:30.744 --> 00:23:33.914
Laena is your daughter. Princess.
Does it bother you?

290
00:23:35.124 --> 00:23:36.333
Of course. it does.

291
00:23:38.419 --> 00:23:41.422
But I understand the order of things.

292
00:23:43.132 --> 00:23:45.551
I'm not sure you do.

293
00:23:48.178 --> 00:23:51.473
If you mean to elicit
some anger from me.

294
00:23:51.557 --> 00:23:54.435
you should know
that you're failing. Princess.

295
00:23:55.227 --> 00:23:56.854
Quite the opposite.

296
00:23:59.857 --> 00:24:01.859
Whether it's to my daughter
or to someone else's.

297
00:24:01.942 --> 00:24:04.945
your father will remarry
sooner than late.

298
00:24:05.863 --> 00:24:08.282
His new wife will produce new heirs.

299
00:24:08.365 --> 00:24:11.243
and chances are. better than not.
that one of those will be male.

300
00:24:11.327 --> 00:24:13.912
And when that boy comes of age
and your father has passed.

301
00:24:13.996 --> 00:24:16.874
the men of the realm
will expect him to be heir.

302
00:24:16.957 --> 00:24:18.375
not you.

303
00:24:20.878 --> 00:24:22.880
Because that is the order of things.

304
00:24:25.215 --> 00:24:27.593
When I'm Queen.
I will create a new order.

305
00:24:29.094 --> 00:24:31.305
How I wish that could be. Rhaenyra.

306
00:24:31.972 --> 00:24:34.475
But the men of the realm
already had their opportunity

307
00:24:34.558 --> 00:24:36.894
to appoint a ruling queen
at the Great Council

308
00:24:36.977 --> 00:24:38.479
and they denied it.

309
00:24:38.562 --> 00:24:41.523
They denied you. Princess Rhaenys.

310
00:24:42.691 --> 00:24:44.485
"The Queen Who Never Was."

311
00:24:45.152 --> 00:24:47.946
But they bent the knee to me
and called me heir to the throne.

312
00:24:48.030 --> 00:24:51.075
Do you remind your father's men of that
as you carry their cups?

313
00:24:55.663 --> 00:24:57.498
Here is the hard truth.

314
00:24:57.581 --> 00:25:00.876
which no one else
has the heart to tell you.

315
00:25:01.627 --> 00:25:04.296
Men would sooner put
the realm to the torch

316
00:25:05.381 --> 00:25:08.384
than see a woman ascend the Iron Throne.

317
00:25:13.180 --> 00:25:15.849
And your father is no fool.

318
00:25:29.613 --> 00:25:32.616
The Small Council
is urging me to remarry.

319
00:25:35.035 --> 00:25:37.454
It seems the realm
wants for a new queen.

320
00:25:42.793 --> 00:25:46.338
A good and kind queen
will give comfort to your subjects.

321
00:25:51.385 --> 00:25:54.388
Does the Small Council
have a particular lady in mind?

322
00:25:56.849 --> 00:26:01.520
Lord Corlys Velaryon has offered
the hand of his daughter.

323
00:26:01.603 --> 00:26:03.230
the Lady Laena.

324
00:26:04.273 --> 00:26:06.275
A very strong match. Your Grace.

325
00:26:07.860 --> 00:26:11.488
I must admit.
I don't know Laena very well.

326
00:26:12.281 --> 00:26:14.616
I'm sure that she is good and kind.

327
00:26:14.700 --> 00:26:18.537
and that she will enjoy your company.
as I have. Your Grace.

328
00:26:33.802 --> 00:26:35.429
I brought you something.

329
00:26:55.991 --> 00:26:58.118
I asked the stonemasons
to mend it.

330
00:27:02.039 --> 00:27:03.999
This is. uh...

331
00:27:04.082 --> 00:27:06.919
a very kind gesture. Alicent.

332
00:27:11.048 --> 00:27:12.048
Very kind.

333
00:27:20.390 --> 00:27:22.309
Come.

334
00:27:24.686 --> 00:27:26.688
The Hand. Your Grace.

335
00:27:31.235 --> 00:27:33.111
Your Grace.
I've called the Small Council

336
00:27:33.195 --> 00:27:34.404
to an emergency session.

337
00:27:34.488 --> 00:27:35.697
Why?

338
00:27:37.115 --> 00:27:39.409
I think it best you hear it directly.

339
00:27:40.786 --> 00:27:41.995
Very well.

340
00:28:12.943 --> 00:28:15.779
- Daemon.
- The Prince left a missive.

341
00:28:15.863 --> 00:28:17.948
which I believe might explain.

342
00:28:18.991 --> 00:28:21.702
"It is the pleasure
of Daemon Targaryen.

343
00:28:21.785 --> 00:28:23.579
the Prince of Dragonstone

344
00:28:23.662 --> 00:28:27.583
and rightful heir to the Iron Throne.

345
00:28:27.666 --> 00:28:30.502
to announce that he is
to take a second wife

346
00:28:30.586 --> 00:28:33.422
in the tradition of Old Valyria.

347
00:28:33.505 --> 00:28:38.594
She is to assume the title
Lady Mysaria of Dragonstone.

348
00:28:38.677 --> 00:28:40.637
Her Grace is with child

349
00:28:40.721 --> 00:28:45.893
and is to have a dragon's egg
placed in the babe's cradle

350
00:28:45.976 --> 00:28:49.271
in the custom of House Targaryen."

351
00:28:49.354 --> 00:28:53.859
The Prince has invited you
to his wedding. Your Grace.

352
00:28:53.942 --> 00:28:57.195
- It is in two days' time.
- Gods be good.

353
00:28:57.279 --> 00:28:59.281
Who is Lady Mysaria?

354
00:28:59.364 --> 00:29:01.284
- We believe...
- Daemon's whore.

355
00:29:03.619 --> 00:29:06.788
- This is nothing less than sedition.
- I strongly agree. sire.

356
00:29:06.872 --> 00:29:09.082
My brother wishes to provoke me.

357
00:29:09.791 --> 00:29:11.752
To answer is to give him what he wants.

358
00:29:11.835 --> 00:29:14.129
The realm is watching. Your Grace.

359
00:29:14.212 --> 00:29:15.756
What would you have me do?

360
00:29:15.839 --> 00:29:17.466
Send him to the Wall?

361
00:29:18.383 --> 00:29:20.385
Perhaps I could put his head on a spike.

362
00:29:20.469 --> 00:29:22.346
Daemon has seized Dragonstone.

363
00:29:22.429 --> 00:29:25.182
has surrounded himself
with an army of Gold Cloaks.

364
00:29:25.265 --> 00:29:27.434
and has now stolen a dangerous weapon.

365
00:29:55.295 --> 00:29:57.381
Assemble a detachment.
Otto.

366
00:29:58.548 --> 00:30:00.425
I will go to Dragonstone
and drag Daemon back

367
00:30:00.509 --> 00:30:02.886
- to face justice myself.
- Your Grace.

368
00:30:04.137 --> 00:30:06.348
My apologies. Your Grace.
but I cannot allow it.

369
00:30:06.431 --> 00:30:08.016
It's too dangerous.

370
00:30:08.100 --> 00:30:10.102
Daemon is without limit.

371
00:30:11.061 --> 00:30:13.230
Let me go to Dragonstone.

372
00:30:40.090 --> 00:30:42.509
You're the most comely girl at court.

373
00:30:43.427 --> 00:30:45.637
Why do you destroy yourself?

374
00:30:46.722 --> 00:30:47.764
Hmm?

375
00:30:51.977 --> 00:30:54.146
Will you see the King tonight?

376
00:30:57.065 --> 00:30:58.483
If you wish it.

377
00:31:01.778 --> 00:31:04.740
- Good day. Ser Criston.
- My lady.

378
00:31:04.823 --> 00:31:07.826
I've assembled 20 of your best
household guards. my Lord Hand.

379
00:31:07.909 --> 00:31:10.120
Sir Harrold will also join us.

380
00:31:14.332 --> 00:31:17.335
Please look after the Hand.
Ser Criston.

381
00:32:37.332 --> 00:32:39.543
Welcome to Dragonstone. Otto.

382
00:32:41.920 --> 00:32:45.006
Your occupation of this island
is at an end.

383
00:32:46.091 --> 00:32:48.093
You're to relinquish the dragon's egg.

384
00:32:48.176 --> 00:32:49.719
disband your army.

385
00:32:49.803 --> 00:32:51.596
banish your whore.

386
00:32:52.764 --> 00:32:55.350
and leave Dragonstone
by order of His Grace.

387
00:32:55.433 --> 00:32:57.853
- King Viserys.
- Where is the King? I don't see him.

388
00:32:57.936 --> 00:33:01.773
His Grace would never lower himself
to entertain such a mummer's farce.

389
00:33:07.154 --> 00:33:08.822
Ser Crispin. wasn't it?

390
00:33:08.905 --> 00:33:10.448
Ser Criston Cole. my Prince.

391
00:33:10.532 --> 00:33:12.659
Ah. yes. apologies. I couldn't recall.

392
00:33:13.076 --> 00:33:15.704
Perhaps my Prince recalls
when I knocked him off his horse.

393
00:33:17.914 --> 00:33:18.914
Very good.

394
00:33:18.957 --> 00:33:21.877
This is a truly pathetic show. Daemon.

395
00:33:21.960 --> 00:33:23.795
Are you so desperate
for the King's attention

396
00:33:23.879 --> 00:33:26.423
that you've resorted to skulking about
like a common cutpurse?

397
00:33:26.506 --> 00:33:29.176
I'm simply keeping
with the traditions of my house.

398
00:33:29.259 --> 00:33:31.011
the same as my brother did for his heir.

399
00:33:31.094 --> 00:33:33.972
Those traditions are for the trueborn
children of royalty.

400
00:33:34.055 --> 00:33:36.892
not for bastards fathered
on a common whore.

401
00:33:37.475 --> 00:33:39.436
Lady Mysaria is to be my wife.

402
00:33:39.519 --> 00:33:40.896
This is an abomination.

403
00:33:40.979 --> 00:33:42.814
With every breath you soil your name.

404
00:33:42.898 --> 00:33:44.691
your house. and your brother's reign.

405
00:33:44.774 --> 00:33:47.986
Our love does not know
titles and traditions.

406
00:33:49.279 --> 00:33:51.573
And what of you. men of the City Watch?

407
00:33:51.656 --> 00:33:53.158
Aiding the Prince in his treason?

408
00:33:53.241 --> 00:33:55.202
The King made me their commander.

409
00:33:55.285 --> 00:33:56.661
They are loyal to me.

410
00:33:57.704 --> 00:33:59.706
You've come for the egg.

411
00:34:01.124 --> 00:34:02.417
Here it is.

412
00:34:03.877 --> 00:34:05.754
Are you mad?

413
00:34:05.837 --> 00:34:08.673
- You'd never survive this.
- Well. happily. neither would you.

414
00:34:09.841 --> 00:34:14.721
To chose violence. here.
is to declare war against your King.

415
00:34:14.804 --> 00:34:16.014
Wonderful.

416
00:34:17.307 --> 00:34:20.602
Even if it ends in the death
of your unborn child and its mother?

417
00:34:59.557 --> 00:35:01.268
All of you.

418
00:35:01.351 --> 00:35:03.353
sheathe the fucking steel.

419
00:36:10.587 --> 00:36:13.631
- What are you doing here. Princess?
- Preventing bloodshed.

420
00:36:13.715 --> 00:36:16.343
Ser Criston. please escort
the Princess to safety.

421
00:36:16.801 --> 00:36:18.762
Take care not to startle Syrax.
my lords.

422
00:36:19.429 --> 00:36:21.222
She's rather protective of me.

423
00:37:11.564 --> 00:37:13.691
I'm right here. Uncle.

424
00:37:15.777 --> 00:37:17.779
the object of your ire.

425
00:37:18.446 --> 00:37:21.324
the reason that you were disinherited.

426
00:37:21.408 --> 00:37:23.701
If you wish to be restored as heir.

427
00:37:23.785 --> 00:37:25.412
you'll need to kill me.

428
00:37:26.621 --> 00:37:27.831
So. do it.

429
00:37:29.082 --> 00:37:31.292
And be done with all this bother.

430
00:39:23.988 --> 00:39:26.950
You announced
that we were to be wed?

431
00:39:28.076 --> 00:39:29.702
On the morrow.

432
00:39:31.329 --> 00:39:33.331
And that I was with child.

433
00:39:34.123 --> 00:39:35.708
Your child.

434
00:39:35.792 --> 00:39:39.045
Well. perhaps when we are wed.
we can make that true.

435
00:39:39.128 --> 00:39:43.091
I ensured long ago that I would never be
threatened by childbirth.

436
00:39:43.174 --> 00:39:46.010
Good. Children can be such
irritating creatures.

437
00:39:46.094 --> 00:39:48.721
You swore to protect me. Daemon.

438
00:39:50.890 --> 00:39:52.559
Dragonstone is quite secure.

439
00:39:55.103 --> 00:39:59.607
Until the King decides
to reclaim his ancestral seat.

440
00:39:59.691 --> 00:40:02.443
His men might not put
the Prince's head on a spike.

441
00:40:02.527 --> 00:40:04.779
but what would they do
with the common whore

442
00:40:04.862 --> 00:40:07.532
he claims he's taken to wife
and made with child?

443
00:40:07.615 --> 00:40:09.242
No one will harm you.

444
00:40:10.368 --> 00:40:14.664
I have been sold as property
more times than I care to count.

445
00:40:14.747 --> 00:40:18.293
beginning in a homeland
I can no longer recall.

446
00:40:19.460 --> 00:40:22.880
Most of my years have been spent
living in terror.

447
00:40:23.673 --> 00:40:25.675
You're safe with me. I swear it.

448
00:40:25.758 --> 00:40:27.135
You are Targaryen.

449
00:40:27.218 --> 00:40:30.388
You can afford to play
your stupid games with the King.

450
00:40:30.471 --> 00:40:32.473
but I cannot.

451
00:40:33.474 --> 00:40:38.187
I didn't come into your service
wanting gold or power

452
00:40:38.271 --> 00:40:39.272
or station.

453
00:40:40.481 --> 00:40:44.277
- I came to you to be liberated.
- Liberated.

454
00:40:47.363 --> 00:40:48.573
From what?

455
00:40:49.866 --> 00:40:51.075
Fear.

456
00:41:18.269 --> 00:41:20.021
No. please. Lord Lyonel.

457
00:41:25.902 --> 00:41:28.821
I have come looking
for an unencumbered opinion.

458
00:41:28.905 --> 00:41:31.282
That's all I would ever give.
Your Grace.

459
00:41:32.200 --> 00:41:33.534
Ever since my name was read

460
00:41:33.618 --> 00:41:35.745
by the archmaesters
at the Great Council.

461
00:41:35.828 --> 00:41:39.207
I have felt Corlys Velaryon's
envious gaze staring at me

462
00:41:39.290 --> 00:41:40.917
from across the Blackwater.

463
00:41:41.793 --> 00:41:45.213
You sit upon the highest seat
in the realm. Your Grace.

464
00:41:45.296 --> 00:41:47.674
Proud men don't like having to look up.

465
00:41:51.636 --> 00:41:52.804
Laena Velaryon.

466
00:41:55.014 --> 00:41:57.392
Lord Corlys is your Master of Ships

467
00:41:58.476 --> 00:42:02.271
and she is the eldest daughter
of the wealthiest house in the realm.

468
00:42:02.355 --> 00:42:06.109
She comes from
unimpeachable Valyrian stock

469
00:42:06.192 --> 00:42:08.820
and she has Targaryen blood.

470
00:42:08.903 --> 00:42:11.989
- What's to mislike?
- She is 12.

471
00:42:12.073 --> 00:42:13.491
She will mature.

472
00:42:15.952 --> 00:42:17.578
I never asked to remarry.

473
00:42:18.246 --> 00:42:21.457
As King.
you have a claim on all things.

474
00:42:22.333 --> 00:42:23.793
Even those you don't want.

475
00:42:23.876 --> 00:42:26.629
Marriage is not an obligation
you can put off for long.

476
00:42:26.713 --> 00:42:29.382
What if I was to reject
Lord Corlys's proposal?

477
00:42:29.465 --> 00:42:31.968
He would not be like to take it well.

478
00:42:32.510 --> 00:42:36.389
I fear nothing short of a direct line
to the Iron Throne would satisfy him.

479
00:42:37.557 --> 00:42:39.976
You should also consider
that we find ourselves

480
00:42:40.059 --> 00:42:42.061
on the precipice of war
in the Stepstones.

481
00:42:43.062 --> 00:42:45.982
And the Sea Snake holds claim to nearly
half the realm's ships.

482
00:42:46.065 --> 00:42:49.152
He would not dare withhold them
in the face of the realm's need.

483
00:42:50.528 --> 00:42:53.906
- Who is he to hector me?
- No one. Your Grace.

484
00:42:55.450 --> 00:42:59.495
But Driftmark makes for a better ally
than it does an enemy.

485
00:43:00.913 --> 00:43:03.124
The Sea Snake
has made a calculated reach.

486
00:43:03.207 --> 00:43:05.376
a fair play for a man of his position.

487
00:43:07.795 --> 00:43:10.173
If you truly want
my unencumbered opinion.

488
00:43:10.256 --> 00:43:11.340
I do.

489
00:43:12.675 --> 00:43:14.844
You should wed Laena Velaryon.
Your Grace.

490
00:43:15.928 --> 00:43:19.390
Sate Lord Corlys
and fix him at your side.

491
00:43:19.474 --> 00:43:20.933
permanently. as an ally.

492
00:43:26.063 --> 00:43:27.440
Your Grace.

493
00:43:27.523 --> 00:43:30.526
the Princess has returned
from Dragonstone.

494
00:43:30.610 --> 00:43:32.236
Dragonstone?

495
00:43:52.256 --> 00:43:53.466
Your Grace.

496
00:43:57.386 --> 00:43:59.555
You disobeyed me.

497
00:43:59.639 --> 00:44:02.642
You fled King's Landing without a word

498
00:44:03.726 --> 00:44:07.355
and you acted without the Crown's leave.

499
00:44:10.441 --> 00:44:12.652
You are my only heir.

500
00:44:13.861 --> 00:44:15.863
You could've been killed.

501
00:44:19.408 --> 00:44:20.827
May I sit?

502
00:44:32.255 --> 00:44:34.549
You went to Dragonstone.

503
00:44:34.632 --> 00:44:36.717
And retrieved the egg without bloodshed.

504
00:44:39.011 --> 00:44:42.223
A feat I'm not sure Ser Otto
could've accomplished alone.

505
00:44:45.268 --> 00:44:47.228
Yes. well...

506
00:44:51.983 --> 00:44:54.569
I sometimes forget
how alike you both were.

507
00:45:04.912 --> 00:45:09.166
Your mother's absence
is a wound that will never heal.

508
00:45:10.501 --> 00:45:12.503
Without her.

509
00:45:12.587 --> 00:45:17.091
the Red Keep has lost a warmth
that I dare say it will never recover.

510
00:45:17.174 --> 00:45:20.386
It pleases me to hear you say this.

511
00:45:24.515 --> 00:45:27.810
To know that I'm not alone in my grief.

512
00:45:27.894 --> 00:45:30.313
I wish I had known better

513
00:45:30.396 --> 00:45:32.648
what to say to you in the aftermath.

514
00:45:35.067 --> 00:45:39.030
I struggled to realize that my daughter
had so quickly become a woman grown.

515
00:45:43.075 --> 00:45:44.702
But I know

516
00:45:45.328 --> 00:45:48.956
she understands
what is now expected of me.

517
00:45:49.040 --> 00:45:51.500
The King must take a new wife.

518
00:45:56.631 --> 00:45:58.841
I could never replace your mother.

519
00:46:01.052 --> 00:46:03.346
No more than I intend
to replace you as heir.

520
00:46:05.139 --> 00:46:07.308
But you are my only heir

521
00:46:07.391 --> 00:46:10.603
and our line is vulnerable.
too easily ended.

522
00:46:11.687 --> 00:46:13.898
And by marrying again.
I may begin to ensure

523
00:46:13.981 --> 00:46:15.399
that we are better defended.

524
00:46:15.483 --> 00:46:16.567
Against whom?

525
00:46:16.651 --> 00:46:18.819
Whomever may dare to challenge us.

526
00:46:25.493 --> 00:46:28.120
I do not wish to make us estranged.

527
00:46:28.955 --> 00:46:30.414
You are the King.

528
00:46:30.957 --> 00:46:34.585
and so. your first duty is to the realm.

529
00:46:37.630 --> 00:46:39.632
Mother would've understood this.

530
00:46:42.259 --> 00:46:43.886
Just as I do.

531
00:47:30.766 --> 00:47:32.768
Good morrow. my lords.

532
00:47:43.946 --> 00:47:47.575
I have decided to take a new wife.

533
00:48:05.926 --> 00:48:07.678
I intend to marry...

534
00:48:14.268 --> 00:48:16.479
the Lady Alicent Hightower...

535
00:48:18.355 --> 00:48:20.357
before spring's end.

536
00:48:27.073 --> 00:48:28.741
This is an absurdity.

537
00:48:29.825 --> 00:48:32.620
My house is Valyrian.

538
00:48:32.703 --> 00:48:34.914
the greatest power in the realm.

539
00:48:36.207 --> 00:48:38.209
And I am your King.

540
00:49:02.817 --> 00:49:04.235
Rhaenyra.

541
00:49:26.590 --> 00:49:30.219
House Velaryon's origins
reach back to Old Valyria.

542
00:49:32.221 --> 00:49:34.849
More ancient even than House Targaryen

543
00:49:36.725 --> 00:49:38.727
according to some texts.

544
00:49:40.146 --> 00:49:41.730
But unlike the Targaryens.

545
00:49:42.815 --> 00:49:44.817
we were no dragonlords.

546
00:49:46.360 --> 00:49:48.988
For centuries.
my house had to scratch out

547
00:49:49.071 --> 00:49:53.075
an existence from the sea
with grit and luck.

548
00:49:55.578 --> 00:49:57.997
When I ascended the Driftwood Throne.

549
00:49:59.165 --> 00:50:00.791
I knew what I wanted.

550
00:50:02.793 --> 00:50:04.795
So I went out and seized it.

551
00:50:06.255 --> 00:50:07.756
Unlike every other lord of the realm.

552
00:50:07.840 --> 00:50:10.885
I can say that I built
my house's high seat

553
00:50:10.968 --> 00:50:13.179
with the strength of mine own back.

554
00:50:19.727 --> 00:50:22.396
I've always thought
of you and I as having been

555
00:50:22.479 --> 00:50:24.315
made from the same cloth.

556
00:50:33.240 --> 00:50:36.076
I wasn't aware you had
a king for a brother.

557
00:50:36.160 --> 00:50:39.663
We're both men who have had
to cut our own way through the world.

558
00:50:40.539 --> 00:50:43.542
We've been passed over too often.

559
00:50:46.337 --> 00:50:47.546
Did you call me to Driftmark

560
00:50:47.630 --> 00:50:50.007
to remind me of my
low standing. Lord Corlys.

561
00:50:50.090 --> 00:50:52.092
or was there some other reason?

562
00:50:55.846 --> 00:50:58.098
You've heard of the troubles
in the Stepstones?

563
00:51:01.185 --> 00:51:05.231
<i>Some Myrish Prince is
feeding Westerosi sailors to the crabs.</i>

564
00:51:05.314 --> 00:51:07.983
<i>I have been petitioning
the King to send my navy</i>

565
00:51:08.067 --> 00:51:09.777
<i>into the territory.</i>

566
00:51:09.860 --> 00:51:12.029
but he's denied me.

567
00:51:12.112 --> 00:51:14.281
It was never
my brother's strongest trait.

568
00:51:14.365 --> 00:51:15.449
What?

569
00:51:16.825 --> 00:51:18.327
Being King.

570
00:51:22.790 --> 00:51:25.167
<i>The Crabfeeder is backed
by powerful entities</i>

571
00:51:25.251 --> 00:51:28.879
<i>within the Free Cities who wish to see
Westeros weakened.</i>

572
00:51:30.965 --> 00:51:34.635
<i>And the King's failures
have allowed him to accumulate strength.</i>

573
00:51:36.428 --> 00:51:38.430
If those shipping lanes fall.

574
00:51:39.473 --> 00:51:41.475
my house will be crippled.

575
00:51:42.309 --> 00:51:44.603
And I will not have Driftmark
beggared while our King

576
00:51:44.687 --> 00:51:48.190
idles himself with feasts.
and balls. and tourneys.

577
00:51:48.274 --> 00:51:51.277
I will speak of my brother as I wish.

578
00:51:53.153 --> 00:51:54.280
You will not.

579
00:51:58.075 --> 00:51:59.868
Waiting in the Stepstones

580
00:51:59.952 --> 00:52:02.204
is a chance for you to prove your worth

581
00:52:02.288 --> 00:52:04.498
to any who might yet doubt it.

582
00:52:06.166 --> 00:52:08.794
We are the realm's second sons. Daemon.

583
00:52:10.254 --> 00:52:12.256
Our worth is not given.

584
00:52:13.799 --> 00:52:15.801
It must be made.

584
00:52:16.305 --> 00:53:16.505
